body:
When you see someone alone, secluded in public and they&#039;re drawing, what compells you to come over and talk to them about it?
&quot;Oh hey what you drawing?&quot;
Oh, yes, let me just stop what I&#039;m doing completely to explain this to you. Thanks. This is exactly what I&#039;m wanting when I open my sketchpad. 
And since it&#039;s often something weird or an original character they always have this mocking smile on their face.
&quot;What do you know how to draw? Just that or people too?&quot;
&quot;How long have you been drawing?&quot;
&quot;Can you draw me?&quot;
No. Stop. 
Just stop.
These are all my least favorite questions in the world.
